{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/zebra-striped-list/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"CSS para impacientes"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"34c19f7d-ea9f-5d26-953b-29c1e6b215fa","excerpt":"Creates a striped list with alternating background colors, which is useful for differentiating siblings that have content spread across a wide row. Explanation…","html":"<p>Creates a striped list with alternating background colors, which is useful for differentiating siblings that have content spread across a wide row.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-html line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>ul</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Item 01<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Item 02<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Item 03<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Item 04<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Item 05<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>li</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>ul</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-css line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">li:nth-child(odd)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background-color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #ddd<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h4>Explanation</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Use the <code class=\"language-text\">:nth-child(odd)</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">:nth-child(even)</code> pseudo-class to apply a different background color to elements that match based on their position in a group of siblings.</li>\n<li>Note that you can use it to apply different styles to other HTML elements like div, tr, p, ol, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Browser support</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://caniuse.com/#feat=css-sel3\">https://caniuse.com/#feat=css-sel3</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://github.com/30-seconds/\">Acesse a Referência original</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"CSS como usar o Zebra striped list","date":"January 04, 2020","description":""}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/zebra-striped-list/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/truncate-text/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"CSS como usar o Truncate text"}}}}}